  "prompt": "What is the best kind of frosting for lemon cake?",
  "response": "The best kind of frosting for lemon cake often depends on personal preference, but several popular options complement the citrusy flavor of the cake beautifully:\n\n1. **Lemon Buttercream Frosting**: This enhances the lemon flavor without overpowering it. Made with butter, powdered sugar, lemon juice, and lemon zest, it creates a smooth and creamy texture that pairs well with lemon cake.\n\n2. **Cream Cheese Frosting**: The tanginess of cream cheese frosting pairs wonderfully with the citrus notes of lemon cake. You can add a touch of lemon zest or juice to align the flavors even more closely.\n\n3. **Lemon Glaze**: For a lighter topping, a simple lemon glaze made from lemon juice and powdered sugar can provide a sweet and tangy finish without the richness of a buttercream or cream cheese frosting.\n\n4. **Swiss Meringue Buttercream**: This frosting has a silky texture that works well with lemon cake. Adding a bit of lemon extract or zest can tie the flavors together nicely.\n\nEach of these options will provide a balanced and flavorful complement to a lemon cake, so you can choose based on the desired texture and level of sweetness.",
